).
 This counter rotation was induced by recesses added to the track.
 The recesses would catch the carriage guides and rotate the spools to compensat
e for the rotation due to movement around the track.
 Adding a retractable part of the track that the guide can push aside was
 found most effective, but rotation can be induced using a fixed track with
 only recesses.
\end_layout

