\begin_layout Standard
The second improvement was to shift the position of the spool carriages
 on the horn gears.
 In the previous design the slots in the horn gears were symmetric, causing
 two spools to be in the same position on opposite sides of the track.
 The carriages experience some positions of higher resistance, the most
 noticeable for the non-twisting cable braider is when pushing on the retractabl
e track section.
 By shifting the spool positions (see figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Offset"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) the machine only has to push a spool carriage through these difficult
 points one at a time instead of two at a time, reducing the torque required
 by the motor and allowing the machine to run faster.
 Breaking the symmetry of the track would have accomplished this as well
 but would have been more complicated.
\end_layout

